BEGIN_PGML
Consider the exponential expression [`\dfrac{x^a\cdot x^b}{x^c}`] where [`\newcommand{\gt}{>}a\gt0, b\gt0\text{,}`] and [`\newcommand{\lt}{<}c \lt 0\text{.}`]
a.  Are there values for [`a\text{,}`] [`b\text{,}`] and [`c`] so that the expression equals [`x^{[$exponent]}\text{?}`] If so, fill in the blanks below with possible values for [`a\text{,}`] [`b\text{,}`] and [`c\text{.}`] If not, fill in the blanks below with the word [|none|]*.

    [`a`] = [_]{$multians}{10}, [`b`] = [_]{$multians}{10}, and [`c`] = [_]{$multians}{10}

a.  Are there values for [`a\text{,}`] [`b\text{,}`] and [`c`] so that the expression equals [`\frac{1}{x^{[$abs]}}\text{?}`] If so, fill in the blanks below with possible values for [`a\text{,}`] [`b\text{,}`] and [`c\text{.}`] If not, fill in the blanks below with the word [|none|]*.

    [`a`] = [_]{$answer}{10}, [`b`] = [_]{$answer}{10}, and [`c`] = [_]{$answer}{10}

END_PGML

############################################################
# Solution
############################################################

BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION
a.  The problem states that [`\frac{x^a\cdot x^b}{x^c}=x^{[$exponent]}\text{.}`] To simplify [`\frac{x^a\cdot x^b}{x^c}\text{,}`] we must add the exponents [`a`] and [`b\text{,}`] and then subtract the exponent [`c\text{.}`] Thus, [`a+b-c`] must equal [`[$exponent]\text{.}`] For example, [`[$a]+[$b]-{[$c]}=[$exponent]\text{.}`]

a.  First off, we must remember that [`\frac{1}{x^{[$abs]}}=x^{[$negexponent]}\text{.}`] The problem states that [`\frac{x^a\cdot x^b}{x^c}=x^{[$negexponent]}\text{.}`] To simplify [`\frac{x^a\cdot x^b}{x^c}\text{,}`] we must add the exponents [`a`] and [`b\text{,}`] and then subtract the exponent [`c\text{.}`] Thus, [`a+b-c`] must equal [`[$exponent]\text{.}`] Since [`a`] and [`b`] are positive, [`a+b`] is a positive number. Then, we have to subtract [`c`] (a negative number), which is the same as adding a positive number. Thus, [`a+b-c`] will result in a positive number, but [` a + b - c `] must equal [$exponent]. Therefore, it is not possible to come up with values for [`a\text{,}`] [`b\text{,}`] and [`c`] that work.

END_PGML_SOLUTION

